125
00:09:04,836 --> 00:09:05,712
May I ask why?

126
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,590
Because of my boss.

127
00:09:15,472 --> 00:09:18,349
I know young people these days
value friendship a great deal,

128
00:09:19,142 --> 00:09:20,894
but it hasn't even been a year.

129
00:09:21,478 --> 00:09:23,229
It's only a shallow friendship.

130
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:26,649
Like you said,

131
00:09:26,733 --> 00:09:29,819
I shouldn't decline your offer
merely because of friendship.

132
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:33,698
But aren't you making this offer
because of my boss?

133
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:40,205
You're immensely interested
in my boss as well as in DanBam.

134
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:42,207
So?

135
00:09:45,043 --> 00:09:48,588
I'm confident that I can grow DanBam.

136
00:09:50,465 --> 00:09:54,385
If you come to notice me, not my boss,
in that process,

137
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:58,348
you can give me
this offer again then, sir.

138
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:24,666
Jo Yi-seo.

139
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:28,128
The manager of Park Saeroyi's pub.

140
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,881
Park Saeroyi, that prick.

141
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:33,716
Because of Mr. Park.

142
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:36,594
He was like a father to me.

143
00:10:59,617 --> 00:11:00,577
Damn it.

144
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:07,000
Jeez, you need to look ahead
when you're driving.

145
00:11:10,879 --> 00:11:13,756
Hey, you can't drive at full speed here.

146
00:11:19,262 --> 00:11:20,346
God damn it.

147
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:26,769
Shall I call my insurer
or just give you money?

148
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:30,481
-What?
-Just answer my question. I'm busy.

149
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:32,066
Jeez, what the...

150
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:34,652
First, you need to apologize to me
for hitting my car.

151
00:11:34,736 --> 00:11:36,404
Are you that rich?

152
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:41,326
Will you say no to money
if I apologize to you?

153
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:44,412
I am rich.

154
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,372
I'm offering you money!

155
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:47,332
What the hell.

156
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:54,422
Here.

157
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:00,303
How's the business going?

158
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:04,474
Not bad. Yi-seo has done some marketing.

159
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:07,143
"Not bad" is an understatement.

160
00:12:07,769 --> 00:12:09,562
We should get ready for the tax season.

161
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:13,441
How much will I be taxed?

162
00:12:14,901 --> 00:12:17,695
Well, I can't really figure out
the exact amount yet.

163
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:19,781
But at this rate, a lot.

164
00:12:21,783 --> 00:12:22,909
What should I do, then?

165
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:26,829
You don't need to worry.
It's my specialty, you know.

166
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:29,958
Let's do this.

167
00:13:08,997 --> 00:13:11,541
I'M GOING TO INCORPORATE DANBAM

168
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,584
I'm going to incorporate DanBam.

169
00:13:13,668 --> 00:13:14,919
PARK SAEROYI

170
00:13:15,003 --> 00:13:17,672
You'll incorporate the business?
So DanBam will become a company?

171
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:20,174
Wow, that means you'll be a CEO.

172
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:23,261
CEO? What does it mean
to incorporate the business?

173
00:13:23,553 --> 00:13:24,679
Incorporate DanBam...

174
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:27,473
What all the money we're pulling in,
we should. For tax purposes.

175
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:30,309
So we need to come up with a name.

176
00:13:31,019 --> 00:13:33,396
A company name. Throw some ideas.

177
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:34,772
DANBAM PUB

178
00:13:34,856 --> 00:13:36,190
"Parkga."

179
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:37,692
What do you think?

180
00:13:37,775 --> 00:13:40,528
PARK SAEROYI

181
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:42,196
No, it sounds like Jangga's copycat.

182
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:44,198
What about "ILL"?

183
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:47,035
I think it sounds cool.

184
00:13:47,243 --> 00:13:49,412
Yi-seo, Royi, love.

185
00:13:49,871 --> 00:13:51,539
PARK SAEROYI

186
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:53,708
Not sure. I don't love it.

187
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:56,294
What about you, Seung-kwon? Got any ideas?

188
00:13:56,878 --> 00:13:57,879
Well...

189
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,048
"Itaewon...

190
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:02,133
Class"?

191
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:04,343
Gosh, what is that?

192
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:05,678
It sounds so lame.

193
00:14:05,762 --> 00:14:07,388
It sounds so uncool, just like him.

194
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:09,807
I actually like it.

195
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:12,018
Right? I like it too.

196
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:13,895
"Itaewon Class."

197
00:14:14,353 --> 00:14:16,105
It's catchy. It's a good name.

198
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:18,107
You guys don't like it?

199
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,234
No, I don't.

200
00:14:20,735 --> 00:14:23,446
"Class," seriously? It sounds so childish.

201
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:25,907
It sounds like something
a teenage bluffer would say.

202
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,034
DANBAM PUB GROUP CHAT

203
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:40,338
SEOMSEOM PUB

204
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,051
ITAEWON

205
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:04,278
The first word that came to my mind
when I heard "Itaewon Class"

206
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:06,864
was "freedom."

207
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,536
A place where
different cultures can mingle freely.

208
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:13,663
Being free from restraints.

209
00:15:14,789 --> 00:15:17,125
Itaewon symbolizes freedom.

210
00:15:19,127 --> 00:15:20,628
That's what you were going for, right?

211
00:15:23,423 --> 00:15:26,134
-Yes.
-Bullshit.

212
00:15:26,217 --> 00:15:28,136
It sounds a little forced,

213
00:15:28,219 --> 00:15:30,304
but it's not bad.

214
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:32,390
It's got that old-school vibe.

215
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:37,311
What can we do? You already love the name.

216
00:15:37,895 --> 00:15:39,397
You'll go with it anyway.

217
00:15:40,565 --> 00:15:41,607
No.

218
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:43,901
I won't if you don't like it.

219
00:15:48,239 --> 00:15:49,824
Well...

220
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:52,660
I'm fine with it if you like it.

221
00:15:53,244 --> 00:15:54,495
It's fine,

222
00:15:54,579 --> 00:15:57,331
but limiting ourselves to Itaewon only
won't help us

223
00:15:57,415 --> 00:16:00,251
when dealing with other businesses.
It makes us look small.

224
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:05,548
Then "Itaewon Class" can be a name
that we use amongst ourselves.

225
00:16:06,132 --> 00:16:07,675
How about we just use the initials?

226
00:16:11,721 --> 00:16:14,223
"IC"?

227
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:16,058
"IC"?

228
00:16:17,435 --> 00:16:19,270
-"IC."
-What?

229
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:23,733
Wow, using English.

230
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:26,777
Nice. It's a memorable name.

231
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:29,113
"IC."

232
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:33,409
I like it.

233
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:36,787
Then since the manager likes it too,

234
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:40,249
we're now the founding members of IC Inc.,

235
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:45,588
Itaewon Class.

236
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:49,467
DANBAM

237
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:54,305
DANBAM

